The paper describes a new approach to machine science that involves human groups interacting to formulate features and provide values for those features that are predictive of some behavioral outcome of interest. This approach involves building a web platform for online collaborative communities, which can lead to exponential increases in content and insight into the causal factors of behavioral outcomes. Given this focus on human-computer interaction and online collaboration, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
